Description: Vessel sherd; earthenware; brown fabric; exterior decorated with horizontal bands, cross-hatching and other geometric motifs in reddish-brown on an orange-brown ground; wheel-turned.Red-brown organic Nile silt with grey-brown core and abundant mica, organic and white inclusions
Curator's comments: See decoration on Coptic painted jar from Karanis (Johnson 1981, pl.14, no.110, 4th to mid 5th century AD). Johnson. B. 1981. Pottery From Karanis: Excavations of the University of Michigan. Kelsey Museum of Archaeology Studies, vol. 7. Ann Arbor: University of Michigan Press.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (IE.15) (Phase 3)
